# Flask Style Guide

*This rule automatically attaches when working with Python files and is available when Flask patterns are relevant.*

**Frontend Integration**: All Flask frontend work should use HTML templates driven through Jinja2. See the frontend rules (`frontend/jinja.mdc`, `frontend/ui-consistency.mdc`, `frontend/html.mdc`, `frontend/css.mdc`, `frontend/javascript.mdc`) for consistent UI/UX patterns.

## Application Structure

- Use **Application Factory Pattern** (`create_app()`)
- Organize routes using **Blueprints**
- Separate configuration by environment (development, production, testing)

## Directory Layout

Follow this standard Flask directory structure:

```
project_root/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py          # Application factory (create_app())
│   ├── config.py            # Configuration classes
│   ├── models.py             # Database models (or models/ package)
│   ├── routes/               # Route blueprints
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   ├── main.py           # Main routes
│   │   ├── auth.py           # Authentication routes
│   │   └── api.py            # API routes
│   ├── templates/            # Jinja2 templates
│   │   ├── base.html         # Base template
│   │   ├── index.html
│   │   └── [feature]/       # Feature-specific templates
│   ├── static/               # Static files
│   │   ├── css/
│   │   │   └── main.css
│   │   ├── js/
│   │   │   └── main.js
│   │   └── images/
│   ├── forms.py              # WTForms (if used)
│   └── utils.py              # Utility functions
├── migrations/               # Flask-Migrate database migrations
├── tests/                   # Test files
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── test_routes.py
│   └── test_models.py
├── instance/                # Instance-specific files (git-ignored)
│   └── config.py            # Local configuration overrides
├── .env                     # Environment variables (git-ignored)
├── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies
└── run.py                   # Application entry point (development)
```

### Key Directory Rules

- **`app/`** - Main application package (not `flask_app/` or `application/`)
- **`app/templates/`** - All Jinja2 templates go here (Flask default)
- **`app/static/`** - All static files (CSS, JS, images) organized by type
- **`app/routes/`** - Organize routes by feature using Blueprints
- **`migrations/`** - Database migrations (Flask-Migrate)
- **`tests/`** - Test files mirror application structure
- **`instance/`** - Instance-specific config (git-ignored, local overrides)

### Template Directory Structure

```
app/templates/
├── base.html                # Base template with common structure
├── components/              # Reusable components
│   ├── nav.html
│   ├── footer.html
│   └── forms/
│       └── user_form.html
├── pages/                   # Page-specific templates
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── about.html
│   └── contact.html
└── errors/                  # Error pages
    ├── 404.html
    └── 500.html
```

### Static Files Organization

```
app/static/
├── css/
│   ├── main.css            # Primary stylesheet
│   ├── components.css       # Component-specific styles
│   └── variables.css       # CSS variables
├── js/
│   ├── main.js             # Primary JavaScript
│   └── components/         # Component-specific JS
└── images/
    ├── logos/
    └── icons/
```

### Blueprint Organization

```python
# app/routes/main.py
from flask import Blueprint

main = Blueprint('main', __name__)

@main.route('/')
def index():
    return render_template('pages/index.html')

# app/routes/auth.py
from flask import Blueprint

auth = Blueprint('auth', __name__, url_prefix='/auth')

@auth.route('/login')
def login():
    return render_template('pages/login.html')
```

